column2: If a country *has a medium or high electricity consumption per person (more than 1300kWh)*, what is the chance (or probability) that it won at least one gold medal in the last Olympics? Give your best guess (between 0 and 1).

If a country *has a low electricity consumption per person (less than 1300kWh)*, what is the chance (or probability) that it won at least one gold medal in the last Olympics? Give your best guess (between 0 and 1).
What is the percentage of countries *having a low electricity consumption per person (less than 1300kWh)*? Give your best guess (between 0 and 1).

If a country *has a medium or low electricity consumption (less than 56 billion kWh)*, what is the chance (or probability) that it won at least one gold medal in the last Olympics? Give your best guess (between 0 and 1).

If a country *has a high electricity consumption (more than 56 billion kWh)*, what is the chance (or probability) that it won at least one gold medal in the last Olympics? Give your best guess (between 0 and 1).
What is the percentage of countries *having a high electricity consumption (more than 56 billion kWh)*? Give your best guess (between 0 and 1).
If a country *does not belong to the Sub Saharan Africa region*, what is the chance (or probability) that it won at least one gold medal in the last Olympics? Give your best guess (between 0 and 1).
If a country *does belong to the Sub Saharan Africa region*, what is the chance (or probability) that it won at least one gold medal in the last Olympics? Give your best guess (between 0 and 1).
What is the percentage of countries *belonging to the Sub Saharan Africa region*? Give your best guess (between 0 and 1).
